Assistance from UNESCO to the University of Concepción -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn the 1960s and 1970s, the educational systems in Spain and Latin America underwent comprehensive and ambitious reforms that took place amid a "revolution of expectations" arising from decolonization, global student protests, and the antagonism between capitalist and communist models of development. Deploying new archival research and innovative perspectives, the contributions to this volume examine the influence of transnational forces during the cultural Cold War. They shed new light on the roles played by the United States, non-state actors, international organizations and theories of modernization and human capital in educational reform efforts in the developing Hispanic world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aCold WarxSocial aspectszLatin America. 0aCold WarxSocial aspectszSpain. 0aCold warxSocial aspectszLatin America. 0aCold warxSocial aspectszSpain. 0aEducation and statezLatin AmericaxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation and statezSpainxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducational changezLatin AmericaxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducational changezSpainxHistoryy20th century. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh  a1960s.  a1970s.  aarchival.  acapitalist.  acold war.  acommunist.  acontemporary history.  acontemporary.  adecolonization.  adevelopment.  aeducation.  aeducational reform.  aglobal.  agovernment.  ahispanic.  ahistory buff.  ahistory.  ainternational.  alatin america.  alatin american.  amodern history.  amodern world.  apolitical.  aprotest.  areform.  areformation.  aresearch.  arevolution.  arevolutionaries.  ascholarly.  